e “dominant eigenvalue”, the “intrinsic rate of growth”, the “asymptotic growth rate”, or simply “the growth rate”. Regardless of which name is chosen, the <italic>λ</italic> is the geometric rate of population change once stage oscillations damp out and the stages approach stable proportions. In other words (<xref rid="ref-1" ref-type="bibr">Caswell, 2001</xref>): <disp-formula id="eqn-4"><label>(4)</label><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="peerj-07-8018-e004.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait"/><tex-math id="M4">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
