  <sec sec-type="methods">
    <title>Methods</title>
    <p>A common life history contains three stages that we define as the juvenile (non-reproducing individual), early adult (with reproduction rates consistent with mid-life fertility), and late adult (with reproduction rates consistent with late-life fertility) stages. We use <italic>A</italic> to represent the PMM for such a species. The characteristic equation for <italic>A</italic> is found in linear algebra textbooks (e.g., <xref rid="ref-9" ref-type="bibr">Strang, 2016</xref>): <disp-formula id="NONUM-d2e854"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="peerj-07-8018-e005.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait"/><tex-math id="M5">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
