    <p>We use the IsoPOPd software to demonstrate the effects on <italic>λ</italic> from hypothetical managerial interventions in white-tailed deer (<italic>Odocoileus virginianus)</italic>. We assume <italic>A</italic> tracks a single sex (female), the <italic>A</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub> are static, the probability of transition in each stage is one, and each <italic>A</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub> constitutes an average for members of the <italic>j</italic>th stage (<xref rid="ref-1" ref-type="bibr">Caswell, 2001</xref>). Let the PMM be (<xref rid="ref-2" ref-type="bibr">Chitwood et al., 2015</xref>), reduced to two digits): <disp-formula id="eqn-11"><label>(11)</label><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="peerj-07-8018-e012.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait"/><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
