        <p>Two dimensions of each orthotope are specified by quadratic interactions of pairwise sets of vital rates, while the third dimension is specified by <italic>λ</italic>. The light blue volume is a negative contribution to <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eqn-12">Eq. (12)</xref>, but a positive contribution to <italic>λ</italic> (<xref rid="table-1" ref-type="table">Table 1</xref>). Should management increase <italic>A</italic><sub>12</sub> or <italic>A</italic><sub>21</sub>, the blue shaded volume will expand. The volumes absent of color represent pairwise sets of matrix elements that have no effect on <italic>λ</italic> at the quadratic scale.</p>
